Explored how DevOps and CI/CD work together to automate building, testing, and deploying software efficiently.
Identified essential tools such as Git, Jenkins/GitHub Actions, Maven, Docker, and Kubernetes commonly used in real-time DevOps pipelines.
Understood how CI/CD pipelines improve reliability by automating code integration, running tests, and deploying applications with minimal manual effort.
Studied Agile methodology, which focuses on iterative development, continuous feedback, and faster delivery of working software.
Reviewed the Waterfall model, a linear and sequential approach where each phase must be completed before moving to the next.
Compared Agile vs Waterfall, learning that Agile supports flexibility and change, while Waterfall is more rigid and structured.
